    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of July 17 article, which misstated location of Avon and Simsbury, Connecticut towns where black New Haven residents say they have been singled out by police for traffic stops</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Monday about complaints by black New Haven residents that they are harassed by police officers from an adjacent town, Hamden, misstated the location of Avon and Simsbury, two other Connecticut towns where the New Haven residents said they had been singled out for traffic stops. It is Hartford County, not Fairfield County.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article on Monday about complaints by black New Haven residents that they are harassed by police officers from an adjacent town, Hamden, misstated the location of Avon and Simsbury, two other Connecticut towns where the New Haven residents said they had been singled out for traffic stops. It is Hartford County, not Fairfield County.</p>
      </block>
